detailedDescription.articleBody:
Joseph Denis Irwin is an Irish former professional footballer who played as a full-back from 1983 to 2004.
Born in Cork, Ireland, he is best known for his long and successful stint at Manchester United, where he established himself as one of the most important players in the United team that won a host of domestic and European trophies in his time there between 1990 and 2002.
